l texts and specific themes. What emerges is an intriguing composite picture of Di Cicco’s complex and unique identikit. The volume includes both scholarly analysis and testimonials by individuals who lived the literary history of which Di Cicco is a part. The inclusion of a bibliography of Di Cicco’s publications and of those about him makes this book a valuable tool for anyone approaching his works for the first time and anyone interested in contemporary North American minority literatures or contemporary Canadian literature.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aLiterary Criticism. 4aLiterary Criticism: Canadian Literature. 4aPoetry. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Poetry.2bisacsh1 aAnselmi, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBillings, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoelhower, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGolini, Vera F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLee, Dennis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoriggio, Francesco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLoriggio, Francesco, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMichele, Mary di, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoritz, Albert F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSenyshyn, Yaroslav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724040uhttps://doi.org/10.51644/978155458106140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781554581061423Coveruhtt